6:
Hmm... It might just be me, but this is
a lot saltier than I was expecting.
9:
Try turning the knob on the fork's
handle slowly to the left. Then give
the food another taste.
14:
Ohh, delightfully sweet! Why, this
doohickey is the perfect companion
for the traveler on the go! I bet they'll
sell like hotcakes!
17:
Then we'll greenlight production. But
first, we need to adapt the battery;
it's much too powerful for a simple
fork.
21:
That'll also save you the trouble of
registering the product as a
restricted artifact! Just leave it to
me!
25:
I'd expect nothing less from a
top-tier merchant.
29:
Me? I'm just a humble purveyor of
wares; nothing compared to the
CEO of a grand corporation!
36:
Feels like I've wandered into a mad
scientist's den, the way you two are
cacklin'.
44: Is that supposed to be a fork?
47:
Yes. You turn the dial on it to change
the flavor of your food. Want to give
it a try?
53:
This still tastes like strawberry
shortcake to me.
57: Strange. The fork IS set to sweet...
63:
Oh, hold on a second! Nimbus is a
beastfolk and his mouth is shaped
differently. The fork may not be
coming into contact with his taste
buds in the same way!
67:
Hmm, I hadn't considered that. We'll
have to redesign the utensil to also
work for beastfolk.
73:
I dunno much about the design, but
it seems to me that if you get this off
the ground, you'll be swimming in
cash.
78:
You betcha! We're looking to earn
capital to set up our venture and
thought the easiest way would be to
enter the gadget market.
81:
By selling tools through the Guild, we
can put our wares out there as part
of a basic equipment pack for
adventurers.
82:
Once there's more demand, we'll
ramp up production. The aim is to
create indispensable everyday
items.
84:
Your world's got a lot of interesting
technology. You could make a
fortune overnight, but that's not
what you're after, is it?
89:
I think trade between Palpebra and
Qualia City will be good for
everyone involved.
95:
And that's why laying down a solid
foundation is important. On that
note, I've got a meeting so I'm going
to skedaddle!
100:
I need to be in Palpebra myself.
Nimbus, would you mind showing
me the way?
105:
Huh? Can't you just go with Mal
Lelucia?
108:
She has her own business to attend
to, and I need a bodyguard. I
promise I'll make it worth your while.
111:
...You're in for a rude awakening if
you think waving cash around will
get you everything you want.
115: Oh... N-no. I didn't mean it that way—
119:
You can just ask me. No need to
make everything a transaction.
123:
Then... I'd like it if we could go
together.
135:
Look at these wares made from
naturally-sourced materials. How
luxurious.
137:
Nobody here uses electronic
payments, and bartering still seems
to be commonplace. If only there
was a way to standardize and
normalize currency...
142:
Your mind's constantly ticking away,
eh?
146:
It was part of my job before to
analyze new concepts and think
about how they affect society on a
larger scale.
148:
I used be a protector of the status
quo, but that's no longer necessary.
Anyway, I guess old habits die hard.
152:
Heh, that's fine. There's no need to
change your personality.
156: Oh... Have I caused a scene?
158:
How many other people do you see
on a floatin' throne? The merchants
are probably wonderin' where they
can stock something similar.
163:
The last thing I want to do is disrupt
Mal Lelucia's business.
164:
...I'll walk. I can put the throne away
until I need it again.
169: You don't have to do that...
173:
It's no big deal. And if anything,
putting my muscles under intense
pressure will force them from their
atrophic state faster...
176:
That sounds like a pretty big deal to
me. *sigh* Here, hop on.
181:
Y-you don't have to carry me! I can
walk!
184:
You're aimin' to be some great
administrator bringing worlds
together, right? Then you've gotta
get a better view to see the whole
picture!
191:
Then let's go to the marketplace! I'd
love to see what kinds of things
people eat here!
192:
Food is the foundation of any
society! By understanding the
common palate, we can start to
look at ways of improving the dining
experience—
195: All right, all right. I get it.
197:
I haven't given anyone a lift on my
shoulders in ages. Make sure you
hold on tight, you hear?
201: Got it! Lead the way, Nimbus!
